(Corrects spelling of Juncker in headline.)  German  Chancellor Angela Merkel  will
host Luxembourgâ€™s Prime Minister  Jean-Claude Juncker  for talks
in the northern German city of Stralsund, in her electoral
district.  Merkel and Juncker, who also heads the group of euro-area
finance ministers, will tour the city at 4 p.m. on Feb. 24 then
give joint statements at about 5 p.m. before they hold
discussions, Steffen Seibert, chief German government spokesman,
said in an e-mailed statement.  The talks will center on the situation in the euro region
and preparations for a March 1-2 summit of European leaders,
